tallation and activation are free; the company charges a monthly monitoring fee of $19.99, placing the system in the average range for top home-security systems. Extra features include full online access to your alarm history and past alerts.","<strong>LiveWatch</strong><br/>Instead of offering renters only one or two home-security package options, LiveWatch offers a variety. You can opt for maximum security or for a less-intensive system. Once you set up the system&#39;s door and window sensors, you can customize your alert preferences. Actions can trigger alerts that go to you or to an entire contact list. In addition to standard alerts for burglary and fire, you can also opt to receive alerts for carbon monoxide or natural-gas leaks.","With installation and activation at no cost and a $9.95 monthly monitoring fee, LiveWatch is an affordable security option for renters.","<strong>Frontpoint</strong><br/>If you&#39;d prefer a home security system for renters that features professional monitoring, Frontpoint is an excellent choice. You can install the system on your own with minimal tools and property modifications. Frontpoint offers a range of door and window sensors, and staff will even help you test or troubleshoot your system to make sure it&#39;s secure. One perk: you can access the live feed from your cell phone.","With its $34.99 monthly price tag installation and activation are free Frontpoint is one of the more expensive home-security system options. This system&#39;s professional monitoring and excellent support accounts for much of the additional cost.","As the top-rated home security systems for apartment renters, Protect America, LiveWatch and Frontpoint give you many options for securing your home. Whether you&#39;re seeking a self-monitoring system, easy access to live streaming or customized alerts, these home security systems are well equipped to protect you and your apartment."]},"id":"e8f6966e-6afc-49d3-a326-715f64349417","type":"text"}]],"body":n